    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
      <![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 167, Number 21 (Thursday, February 4, 2021)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href="https://www.gpo.gov">www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. SCALISE:H.R. 837.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:The First Amendment guarantees both free speech and thefree exercise of religion. The Free Speech Fairness Actrestores these fundamental liberties to churches andnonprofits.[Page H388]</pre>]]>
